<subSubSection id="45814297CA9A94E13BCA078D915A2159" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="C5BC3732E7BBA6F2254757496D7ED284" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="189A23BD3B89EBE5AA5F124501B43FAC" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">
This species was described from a single female specimen (holotype) from Taiwan. Both Andy Hamilton and Masami Hayashi (pers. comm.) examined the type (Entomological Institute, Hokkaido University, Sapporo, Japan) and the 
<normalizedToken id="459A8F24FED9066044F8675991674FB2" originalValue="latter’s">latter's</normalizedToken>
photographs of the type are reproduced here (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="A8FCB5D22E3F4819F69FC111D64408C9" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Matsumura Taiwan Idiocerine species A, B Idiocerus apicalis, dorsal and lateral, habitus respectively (holotype) C, D I. formosanus, dorsal and lateral, habitus respectively (syntype). Photographs by Masami Hayashi." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.76731.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/671696" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">5A, B</figureCitation>
). The holotype bears a determination label by Andy Hamilton indicating the species belongs to 
<taxonomicName id="9EB24A198FEB267DEA58FBE95EB599E8" authorityName="Freytag &amp; Morrison" authorityYear="1972" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Balocerus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Balocerus" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4639C394CA4720F262F71BD06BBB6438" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">Balocerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but this needs to be confirmed, particularly as the specimen is female. The label information on the specimen is as follows (hw = handwritten, pr = printed):
</paragraph>
<caption id="5E96E8BA938B54BFB28C9BC12FA12CDF" doi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.76731.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/671696" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" start="Figure 5" startId="F5">
<paragraph id="DF805EBA90B1D62CFE97C0E4EF8AD755" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">
<emphasis id="172F6F02C4A648F3523A0A1EFCCCFD96" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">Figure 5.</emphasis>
Matsumura Taiwan Idiocerine species 
<emphasis id="CDD4341154730EEED34C42E759971C27" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">A, B</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="92857076B3093276822327A694F20D01" authorityName="Matsumura" authorityYear="1912" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Idiocerus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Idiocerus apicalis" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apicalis">
<emphasis id="CF829660FE72DBFC6D02A3BAA478C01E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">Idiocerus apicalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, dorsal and lateral, habitus respectively (holotype) 
<emphasis id="DC909EA4A45F5587BC8C4266DD45A415" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">C, D</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="993FA84E422B84E1AB0C9A112531C2B7" genus="I." lsidName="I. formosanus" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" rank="species" species="formosanus">
<emphasis id="5E647DFFD08B631D621EC07DDA3DD5F9" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">I. formosanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, dorsal and lateral, habitus respectively (syntype). Photographs by Masami Hayashi.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="6EBB22EDA199AABD4D8311320E72E594" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">
<taxonomicName id="671CB6F339FF8ED0265530AF8C6575D1" genus="I." lsidName="I. apicalis" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" rank="species" species="apicalis">
<emphasis id="E15DDBCF1081F84FAF2CC0062B3C04BA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">I. apicalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. (hw), det. Matsumura (pr)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CB1F9A412D1FDE69CDC049F8D289293E" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">Formosa, Matsumura (printed), (underside) Toroen, 19/4 '07 (hw)</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B783F00882B9CC8A0AAAFE26A679BDA2" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">
Holotype (red label, printed), 
<taxonomicName id="0D6AADE47F7FDA0F224711F1125C95D6" authorityName="Matsumura" authorityYear="1912" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Idiocerus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Idiocerus apicalis" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apicalis">
<emphasis id="9DA792384F2D26AFEA0885F8257DE310" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">Idiocerus apicalis</emphasis>
